rComments: I have never fallen asleep in his lectures, and trust me that says a lot. He is caring, funny, and makes lectures enjoyable - even the 2 hour ones. His notes make sense if you go to lecture. The textbook is good but it gets confusing really fast. His tests are easy - fair (gets harder through the year). I love him; good prof.
This guy is an OG. Really experienced and knows his stuff. Really enjoyed this class!
I want to be a professor like him someday. Attitude matters a lot and you will learn a lot from him and study!!

Perfect prof.! Knows the stuff really well and teaches it really simply. Doesn't make you memorize any formulas but expects you to really understand the subject and makes exams according to that. If you attend all the lectures, you don't need any textbooks at all. Also real life examples are given in lectures relating to materials!

I liked him from MIE231 but in MIE221, he was unclear. He taught for brief time and he did not tell how to answer his questions in a proper way. His questions were open ended and making it hard to determine what will he desire for such an answer.

Knowledgeable professor with great humor. It seems that he really cares and likes his students. I especially like the way that he spends 10 minutes to explain the concept crystal clear and then joke for the rest 40 minutes :) Beno is an asset to U of T.

Prof is very funny and good at explaining concepts with examples. Likes to ensure the entire class understands a concept before moving on, which takes up class time. Very helpful before exams. Tests are fair.
OH NOEEES THE MUSTACHE IS GOOOOONE
A fun prof who was very dedicated, especially on the blackboard forums when students had questions the day before a test. Tests were fair and the lectures were enjoyable.

BENO!! Funniest prof ever, but still got his point across and made sure EVERYONE understood what he taught before he would move on. Made fun of Alex...lol... and pretty much anyone who asks stupid questions.

He was the worst prof I ever had. If you're serious about engineering he's not good. Sure he makes lots of jokes and is funny, but at the expense of class time and material. We were over 3 lec behind bcs of his jokes. I learned everything from the book. Can't give a serious answer to student questions. Wastes so so much time on stupid jokes.
It sometimes becomes difficult to tell whether he's joking or serious. Many people find it difficult to ask him questions.
extremely useful class + jokes + a lot of fun...Unforgetable large class experience...and I suspect that he can remember everyone's face+name in his class........

awesome guy, makes the best jokes and flies through the material, but still makes it easy for everyone to understand. its always fun when its beno's class. hehe said he'd never buy a lottery ticket and then the next day 3 uT profs win a jackpot =P
cool teacher, its been like 4 yrs but i still remeber him because he was extremely helpful and kept the class interesting.
Hilarious.  Rewards stupid questions with deserving answers.  Confrontational, which keeps class interesting (Hard to do when you teach statistics).
Beno is the greatest...hilarious...two thumbs up!!
